com.fxgraph.graph

Interface ICell

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IGraphNode
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SequenceDiagram.IActorCell
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCell, CartesianPoint, RectangleCell, SequenceDiagram.ActorCell, TriangleCell

    public interface ICell
extends IGraphNode
    Interface that any graph cell must implement. A cell is a hierarchical graph node that can have child cells and parent cells. Each cell has references to both its children and its parents. However, note that a cell can add and remove children, but can so far only add parents (not remove them).
    Author:
    sirolf2009, ogallagher (javadoc)
